Goal: Reproduce the empty-array crash bug, write a test, then fix it

flow:
  prompt: Read the bug report in TASK.md. Reproduce the crash by calling filterByCompany with a nonexistent company, then passing the result to getStatistics(). Confirm it crashes.
  prompt: Write a failing test in src/test.js that demonstrates the crash: call getStatistics([]) and filterByCompany(contacts, 'Nonexistent') then getStatistics on the result.
  run: node src/test.js
  prompt: Now fix getStatistics() in src/contacts.js to handle empty arrays gracefully. Return sensible defaults (total 0, averageAge 0, topCompany null, youngest null, oldest null). Also fix getSummary() to handle the empty case.
  until command_succeeded max 3
    run: node src/test.js
    if command_failed
      prompt: Tests still failing. Fix the remaining issues: ${last_stdout}
    end
  end

done when:
  file_exists src/contacts.js
